{"number":117,"title":"CopyPasteDialog clipboard fallback uses deprecated execCommand and shows visible textarea","body":"## Summary

In `src/components/CopyPasteDialog.tsx` (lines 32-37), the clipboard fallback uses the deprecated `document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)`. The fallback textarea also lacks positioning styles, so it&#39;s briefly visible on screen before being removed.

## Location

`src/components/CopyPasteDialog.tsx:27-46`

## Details

```typescript
const handleCopyAndProceed = async () =&gt; {
    try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(prompt);
    } catch {
        const textarea = document.createElement(&#39;textarea&#39;);
        textarea.value = prompt;
        document.body.appendChild(textarea);
        textarea.select();
        document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;);  // deprecated
        document.body.removeChild(textarea);
    }
```

Issues:
1. `document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;)` is deprecated
2. The textarea lacks `style.position = &#39;fixed&#39;` and `style.opacity = &#39;0&#39;`, so it&#39;s briefly visible
3. No error handling in the fallback path

## Suggested Fix

Option A: Remove the fallback entirely. All browsers that support React 19 also support `navigator.clipboard.writeText()`.

Option B: If keeping the fallback, add positioning to hide the textarea:
```typescript
const textarea = document.createElement(&#39;textarea&#39;);
textarea.value = prompt;
textarea.style.position = &#39;fixed&#39;;
textarea.style.opacity = &#39;0&#39;;
textarea.style.left = &#39;-9999px&#39;;
document.body.appendChild(textarea);
textarea.select();
document.execCommand(&#39;copy&#39;);
document.body.removeChild(textarea);
```

## Severity

Low — the fallback is rarely triggered and the visual flash is very brief.","state":"open","html_url":"https://github.com/DrDonik/ai-recipe-planner/issues/117","user":{"login":"DrDonik","id":7161789,"profile_url":"https://github.com/DrDonik","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7161789?v=4"},"author_association":"OWNER","labels":["enhancement","validated","complexity:easy","ux:positive","auto-implementable"],"comments":3,"reactions":{"total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"hooray":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"created_at":"2026-02-15T12:21:13Z","updated_at":"2026-02-16T20:58:25Z"}

