{"pageInfo":{"endCursor":"REDACTED","hasNextPage":false,"hasPreviousPage":false,"startCursor":"REDACTED"},"reviewThreads":[{"ID":"PRRT_kwDOQ2QcK85u66hM","IsResolved":false,"IsOutdated":false,"IsCollapsed":false,"Comments":{"Nodes":[{"ID":"PRRC_kwDOQ2QcK86nur2x","Body":"**Missing error handling for clipboard operation**

This change removes all error handling from the clipboard write operation. If `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` fails (due to permissions, browser security settings, or other reasons), the function will throw an unhandled promise rejection, but the user will still see "Copied!" feedback and advance to the paste step - even though the copy actually failed.

This violates the error handling requirements in [AGENTS.md:205](https://github.REDACTED.md#L205):
> **Error Handling**: User-facing errors displayed via `error` state in App.tsx

While this rule mentions App.tsx specifically, the principle applies: user-facing operations that can fail need error handling to inform the user.

**Suggested fix:** Add error handling to notify users when clipboard operations fail. The component already has an `error` state that could be used for this purpose:

```typescript
const handleCopyAndProceed = async () => {
    try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(prompt);
        setCopied(true);
        // Advance to paste step after a brief moment to show "Copied!" feedback
        setTimeout(() => {
            setStep('paste');
        }, 500);
    } catch (err) {
        setError(t.errorCopyingPrompt || 'Failed to copy to clipboard. Please try again.');
    }
};
```

This ensures users are notified if the copy operation fails, preventing confusion when they try to paste.","Path":"src/components/CopyPasteDialog.tsx","Line":28,"Author":{"Login":"claude"},"CreatedAt":"2026-02-16T21:02:53Z","UpdatedAt":"2026-02-16T21:02:54Z","URL":"https://github.com/DrDonik/ai-recipe-planner/pull/138#discussion_r2814033329"}],"TotalCount":1}},{"ID":"PRRT_kwDOQ2QcK85u66l4","IsResolved":false,"IsOutdated":false,"IsCollapsed":false,"Comments":{"Nodes":[{"ID":"PRRC_kwDOQ2QcK86nur8d","Body":"**Missing tests for modified code behavior**

This PR modifies code behavior by removing error handling and the fallback mechanism, but includes no tests for the CopyPasteDialog component.

This violates the testing requirements in [AGENTS.md:95](https://github.REDACTED.md#L95):
> **All code changes must include tests** — new features need new tests, modified code needs updated tests.

And [AGENTS.md:283](https://github.REDACTED.md#L283):
> Add or update tests in `src/__tests__/` for all changed behavior.

This isn't a cosmetic change - it materially alters how the component handles clipboard API failures (from "never throws" to "may throw").

**Required action:** Add tests for CopyPasteDialog in `src/__tests__/components/CopyPasteDialog.test.tsx` that cover:
- Successful clipboard copy operation
- Clipboard API failure scenarios (permissions denied, API not available)
- UI state updates (copied state, step progression)
- Error display (if error handling is added per the other comment)","Path":"src/components/CopyPasteDialog.tsx","Line":28,"Author":{"Login":"claude"},"CreatedAt":"2026-02-16T21:03:05Z","UpdatedAt":"2026-02-16T21:03:05Z","URL":"https://github.com/DrDonik/ai-recipe-planner/pull/138#discussion_r2814033693"}],"TotalCount":1}},{"ID":"PRRT_kwDOQ2QcK85v7-o6","IsResolved":false,"IsOutdated":false,"IsCollapsed":false,"Comments":{"Nodes":[{"ID":"PRRC_kwDOQ2QcK86pEpBc","Body":"**Bug: unhandled promise rejection breaks the dialog flow**

Removing the `try/catch` entirely means that if `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` rejects — which can happen when the page loses focus, when clipboard permission is denied, or under certain iframe/permissions-policy configurations — the rejection propagates unhandled from the async event handler.

As a result:
- `setCopied(true)` is **never called** → no "Copied!" feedback
- The `setTimeout` to advance to step 2 **never runs** → user is silently stuck on the copy step
- React's `ErrorBoundary` does **not** catch unhandled promise rejections from event handlers, so there is no fallback UI either

Dropping the deprecated `execCommand` fallback is correct, but the `try/catch` wrapper itself should be retained (with an empty or informative `catch` body) so the dialog always advances regardless of clipboard success:

```suggestion
        try {
            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(prompt);
        } catch {
            // Clipboard write failed — user can copy the prompt text manually
        }
```

